# Local Air Hockey

A real-time multiplayer air hockey game and chat application built with Node.js, Socket.IO, and Matter.js physics engine.

## Features

- Real-time air hockey gameplay with physics simulation
- Two-player paddle control (Blue: W/A/S/D, Red: I/J/K/L)
- Paddle control assignment and release
- Live chat between connected users
- Score tracking and goal detection

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/) (v10 or higher recommended)
- npm (comes with Node.js)

### Installation

1. Clone or download this repository.
2. Open a terminal in the project directory.
3. Install dependencies:

   ```sh
   npm install
   ```

### Running the Server

Start the server with:

```sh
node Server.js
```

The server will start on port 3000 by default.

### Playing the Game

1. Open your browser and go to [http://localhost:3000/chatClient.html](http://localhost:3000/chatClient.html)
2. Enter your name in the chat input to join.
3. To control a paddle:
   - Press `1` for Blue paddle (W/A/S/D to move)
   - Press `2` for Red paddle (I/J/K/L to move)
   - Press `0` to release paddle control
4. Chat with other users in the text area.

## Project Structure

```
Server.js                # Main server file (Node.js + Socket.IO + Matter.js)
package.json             # Project dependencies
www/
  airhockey.png          # Air hockey table image
  canvas.js              # Client-side game and chat logic
  chatClient.html        # Main client HTML page
```

## Dependencies

- [socket.io](https://socket.io/)
- [matter-js](https://brm.io/matter-js/)

